The Akwa Ibom chapter of the APC Grassroots Movement in support of President Muhammadu Buhari has urged Senator Bassey Akpan of the PDP to steer clear of the development programmes of the governing APC. The group said Sen. Akpan who represents Akwa Ibom North-East had been seen lately championing some of the development policies of the APC allegedly for ulterior motives. In a statement yesterday, the National Coordinator of the group, Com. Mike George, said the attempt by Sen. Akpan to disrupt the confirmation of Sen. Godswill Akpabio as a member of President Buhari’s cabinet was uncalled for. Com George said Sen. Akpan had through a “failed Point of Order” tried to stop the confirmation of Akpabio. Bedlam in Senate over sitting arrangement PDP, senator allege planned ‘takeover’ of A’Ibom by APC Akwa Ibom APC will force way into stadium for Buhari's campaign - Presidential Aide Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin